&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Evangelism:&lt;/strong&gt; Identify and penetrate &quot;Big AI&quot; accounts (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Meta, etc.) and emerging innovators in the Real-time Voice/LLM space to position Bandwidth as the premier platform for high-scale, low-latency voice integration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Strategy &amp;amp; Licensing:&lt;/strong&gt; Design and execute the framework for licensing Bandwidth’s unique voice data assets for AI training, ensuring compliance, ethical standards, and high commercial value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Relationship Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Navigate complex organizational structures to build &quot;at-level&quot; partnerships with C-suite executives, Product Leads, and Head of Research counterparts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product-Market Feedback Loop:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as the &quot;voice of the AI customer&quot; internally. Gather technical requirements and friction points to collaborate with Product and Engineering teams on rapid iterations of our AI feature set.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ecosystem Mapping:&lt;/strong&gt; Stay at the bleeding edge of AI trends (Text-to-Speech, Speech-to-Text, and Real-time Voice) to identify new areas where Bandwidth can create &quot;moats.&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Making:&lt;/strong&gt; Define the &quot;Voice for AI&quot; category for Bandwidth. This includes creating partnership structures that prioritize technical integration and long-term ecosystem alignment over short-term transaction volume.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
