&lt;p&gt;At &lt;strong&gt;Bandwidth&lt;/strong&gt;, we shape how the world connects. We&#39;re the global communications software company and Tier 1 network operator with global reach.&amp;nbsp; The voice, messaging, and emergency services infrastructure behind the brands and apps you use every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Because we own the network we build on,&lt;em&gt; the problems you&#39;ll solve here are bigger, more complex, and more impactful. &lt;/em&gt;And as communications shifts to AI, we&#39;re the infrastructure layer making it possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We call ourselves BANDmates because building something this big takes collaboration, different perspectives, and the freedom to bring your authentic self to the table.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re experts who speak like humans. Ready to build what&#39;s next? &lt;strong&gt;#JoinTheBand&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Are Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position within the CLEC product team will focus on the Bandwidth and market evolution to IP connectivity, with the goal of removing all TDM interconnections. You will lead commercial negotiations with other carriers to add IP interconnections where they are not currently in place.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;Senior Product Manager&lt;/strong&gt; at Bandwidth, is responsible for leading and driving the execution of new product introduction, from inception to deployment. You will define requirements and lead execution to the market. You will have a long-term vision with your approach to problems and can pivot on short notice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a strategy to support the IP evolution of Bandwidth as it interacts with carriers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify targeted companies and negotiate agreements supporting IP interconnection.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross functionally to establish connectivity and turn up carriers under the new agreements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead market validation and customer discovery efforts for incubated initiatives. Target markets may include specific industry verticals, wholesale telecom services, consumer communications services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make informed decisions on product evolution based on metrics collected with each customer interaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with senior leadership to establish a steady flow of new technology and service opportunities through external awareness events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement go to market strategy, ensuring an understanding of the product positioning, key benefits and target customers, working closely with marketing and sales.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate as key member in cross-discipline team composed of Sales, Marketing, Operations, and Engineering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education: &amp;nbsp;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in field with 10+ years of experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience:&amp;nbsp;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous startup experience is a strong plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in telecommunications and SaaS business delivery models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;History of commercial negotiation success, especially if targets within telecommunications working with Local Exchange Carriers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regulatory background related to telecommunications is a strong plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must work well in early-stage startup environments, where direction may pivot multiple times in a month based on market feedback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of telecom services and associated protocols (SIP, RTP, G.7xx, SMPP, WebRTC) helpful for success in this role&lt;/li&

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bandwidth&lt;/strong&gt;, a prior “Best of EC” award winner, is a global software company that helps enterprises deliver exceptional experiences through voice, messaging, and emergency services. Reaching 65+ countries and over 90 percent of the global economy, we&#39;re the only provider offering an owned communications cloud that delivers advanced automation, AI integrations, global reach, and premium human support.&amp;nbsp;Bandwidth is trusted for mission-critical communications by the Global 2000, hyperscalers, and SaaS builders!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Bandwidth, your music matters when you are part of the BAND. &amp;nbsp;We celebrate differences and encourage BANDmates to be their authentic selves. &amp;nbsp;#jointheband&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Senior Software Engineer to take an AI voice agent platform from working concept to shipping, revenue-generating product.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This isn&#39;t an R&amp;amp;D role. The research phase proved the concept works. The engine runs — now we need to build the car around it. We&#39;re looking for someone who builds products — someone who ships code to real customers, watches how they use it, and ships again next week. You&#39;ll be joining a small, high-caliber team with deep voice and telephony expertise, and your job is to help us turn that foundation into a SaaS platform that resellers can white-label and deploy for thousands of SMBs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Innovation Studio operates like a startup — backed by the infrastructure of a public company. We optimize for learning speed, not perfection. If you&#39;ve spent your career inside enterprise release processes and that&#39;s where you&#39;re comfortable, this isn&#39;t the right fit. If you&#39;ve been waiting for a team that ships at the pace of a startup but sits on top of a global communications network — keep reading.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You Work Matters As Much As What You Know:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a senior IC role. You lead by example, not management authority.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engineering Fundamentals Are Non-Negotiable: You understand software design, system architecture, and why things break at scale — not because you read about it, but because you&#39;ve built through it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Product Shipping Experience: You&#39;ve built and launched products that real customers use — ideally in a startup or high-growth environment. Prototypes and POCs don&#39;t count.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI as a Force Multiplier, Not a Crutch: You&#39;ve embraced AI development tools as a core part of how you work. You use AI to move faster while your experience and judgment ensure the output is sound.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep Instincts Over Blind Trust: When AI generates code, you know whether it&#39;s good — and more importantly, you know when it&#39;s subtly wrong.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full-Stack Fearlessness: When you hit an unfamiliar domain, your instinct is to pick it up and move fast — using AI to operate across the full stack without sacrificing quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This combination — strong fundamentals amplified by AI fluency — is a first-class requirement, not a nice-to-have.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ship the Product: Build the SaaS platform layer that turns our AI voice agent into a multi-tenant, revenue-generating product — tenant management, partner APIs, configuration workflows, onboarding UX, operational dashboards, and the glue that holds it all together.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work Everywhere in the Stack: Backend services, frontend, infrastructure, AI pipeline — you go where the highest-priority work is. Role boundaries slow teams down; you ignore them.&lt;/li&gt;
